At least nine climbers were killed today and another six were reported missing after they were hit by an avalanche on the world's eighth-highest mountain.

The team, which included French and German climbers, got into difficulty on the slopes of Mount Manaslu in the Himalayas of northern Nepal.

Police official Basanta Bahadur Kuwar said the bodies of a Nepalese guide and a German man had been recovered.

