Weather conditions were deteriorating and it was not possible to continue air searches of the mountain this afternoon, Kuwar said.

The identities of the victims were still being confirmed.

The avalanche happened as the climbers were at a camp 22,960ft high.

They had been preparing to head towards the mountain's 26,760ft summit

It is the beginning of Nepal's autumn mountaineering season.

